original_title: Bronx: Westchester Avenue - St. Peter's Avenue
text:
2511 Westchester Avenue(right), at the N.E. corner of St. Peters Avenue, showing the parish house of St. Peters Protestant Episcopal Church and the old carriage sheds. In the left background is Public School No. 12, on Frisby Avenue.

Brown Brothers
June, 1926

original_title: Bronx: Westchester Avenue - St. Peter's Avenue
text:
2511 Westchester Avenue, at the N. E. corner of St. Peters Avenue, showing the Parish House of St. Peters Protestant Episcopal Church, seen from the latter Avenue. View 3 shows the old carriage sheds in rear of the house, on St. Peters Avenue. Shown, too, is the rear of an apartment house fronting on Frisby Avenue.

July 9, 1928
Views 1,2,3
